<inglise> COUNCIL REGULATION (EC) No 411/98 of 16 February 1998 on additional animal protection standards applicable to road vehicles used for the carriage of livestock on journeys exceeding eight hours </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 411/98 loomade kaitse t&auml;iendavate normide kohta, mida kohaldatakse eluskarja vedavatele maantees&otilde;idukitele &uuml;le kaheksa tunni kestva veo puhul 16. veebruar 1998 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Directive 91/628/EEC of 19 November 1991 on the protection of animals during transport (1), and in particular Article 13(1) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 19. novembri 1991. aasta direktiivi 91/628/EM&Uuml;, milles k&auml;sitletakse loomade kaitset vedamise ajal, (1) eriti selle artikli 13 l&otilde;iget 1, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas under Article 5(A) (1) (c) of Directive 91/628/EEC it is necessary to lay down the requirements applicable to means of transport that will ensure compliance with Community requirements concerning animal welfare and in particular those to be laid down in accordance with Article 13(1); </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: direktiivi 91/628/EM&Uuml; artikli 5 A l&otilde;ike 1 punktiga c on vaja s&auml;testada transpordivahendite suhtes kohaldatavad n&otilde;uded, mis vastaksid &uuml;henduse n&otilde;uetele loomade heaolu kohta, eriti artikli 13 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is necessary, when domestic solipeds and domestic animals of the bovine, ovine, caprine and porcine species are transported on journeys exceeding eight hours, to lay down standards applicable to the type of transport covered by this Regulation additional to those laid down in Chapter VII(3) of the Annex to Directive 91/628/EEC for the means of transport used; </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;rusega on vaja s&auml;testada direktiivi 91/628/EM&Uuml; lisa VII peat&uuml;ki l&otilde;ikega 3 etten&auml;htud transpordiliikidele t&auml;iendavad normid, mida kohaldatakse koduloomadena peetavate kabjaliste, veiste, lammaste, kitsede ja sigade veol &uuml;le kaheksa tunni kestva teekonna puhul kasutatavate transpordivahendite suhtes; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas animals of the species concerned are mostly transported by road; whereas it is therefore appropriate in an initial stage to lay down the additional standards with which road vehicles must comply if they are to be used for carriage of animals of the species concerned on journeys exceeding eight hours; </inglise>
<eesti> k&otilde;nealustesse liikidesse kuuluvaid loomi veetakse peamiselt m&ouml;&ouml;da maanteid; seet&otilde;ttu on asjakohane s&auml;testada k&otilde;igepealt t&auml;iendavad normid, millele peavad vastama maantees&otilde;idukid, mida kasutatakse k&otilde;nealustesse liikidesse kuuluvate loomade puhul &uuml;le kaheksa tunni kestval veol; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, however, these additional standards with which road vehicles must comply are laid down without prejudice to measures likely to be adopted subsequently concerning additional standards applicable to the carriage of livestock by other means of transport, in particular transport by train and by sea; whereas pending the adoption of such future measures, the provisions of Chapter VII(3) of the Annex to Directive 91/628/EEC continue to apply to the carriage of livestock by such other means of transport; </inglise>
<eesti> on s&auml;testatud t&auml;iendavad normid, millele peavad vastama maantees&otilde;idukid, ilma et see piiraks edaspidi v&otilde;etavaid meetmeid t&auml;iendavate normide osas, mida kohaldatakse eluskarja muude transpordivahendite suhtes, eriti raudtee- ja meretranspordi suhtes; k&otilde;nealuste edaspidiste meetmete vastuv&otilde;tmiseni j&auml;tkatakse muude transpordivahendite puhul direktiivi 91/628/EM&Uuml; lisa VII peat&uuml;ki l&otilde;ike 3 kohaldamist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas to ensure the welfare of the animals concerned, the additional standards must lay down certain specific obligations with regard notably to access to the vehicle, separation of animals by moveable partition, detailed arrangements concerning feeding and watering and adequate ventilation based either on a forced ventilation system or on a system which will ensure compliance with a prescribed temperature range; </inglise>
<eesti> asjaomaste loomade heaolu tagamiseks peab t&auml;iendavate normidega ette n&auml;gema teatavad konkreetsed kohustused eelk&otilde;ige veokite ligip&auml;&auml;setavuse kohta, loomade &uuml;ksteisest eraldamise kohta teisaldatavate vaheseinte abil, loomade s&ouml;&ouml;tmise ja jootmise &uuml;ksikasjaliku korra kohta ning piisava ventilatsiooni kohta, mis p&otilde;hineb kas sundventilatsioonis&uuml;steemil v&otilde;i s&uuml;steemil, millega tagatakse kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud temperatuur; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the choice of one or the other of the above systems must not prejudice the principle of the free movement of the animals, </inglise>
<eesti> kummagi eespool nimetatud s&uuml;steemi valik ei tohi piirata loomade vaba liikumise p&otilde;him&otilde;tet, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
